        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-12-01 13:55:56.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nopenssl is under apache v2 so no license problem at this level\nI have some questions\nas any change here may have impacts in several projects..\n\n- are we sure we need to install it at the system level on top of the alpine?\n- how do the java components proceed for the openssl installation?\n- are we sure that the version follows seccom recommendation? https://git.onap.org/integration/seccom/tree/recommended_versions.yaml",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "69a40e4664c6c87b266be0904c3512e2d7678c89",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 57,
          "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pd1248@att.com",
          "username": "pdragosh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-12-01 14:04:14.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "074ed5739e4949141c25dfc934c8a4a116a12df3",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 6714,
          "name": "Jan Malkiewicz",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jan.malkiewicz@nokia.com",
          "username": "jmalkiewicz"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-12-01 14:06:38.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Morgan, we need openssl because we need to covert certificates to PEM format (see commit https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/oom/+/115027)",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "1b8667a30b0c1c423ca8f7e942f5c45706f1c6ba",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1215,
          "name": "Morgan Richomme",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "morgan.richomme@orange.com",
          "username": "mrichomme"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-12-01 14:09:54.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> Hi Morgan, we need openssl because we need to covert certificates to PEM format (see commit https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/oom/+/115027)\n\nyes I know, my only question is\nshall it be integrated in the baseline image \nor shall be added in the image inheriting from the baseline image (1 level up)\n\nin the baseline we have the minimum stuff that is supposed to be used by everybody\nI agree that openssl is probably a global need\nbut as far as I know current projects inheriting the baseline image are already dealing with openssl\nit is just to understand..\nbut as indicated in the chat I have no objection to merge",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "65d7c778cbb457371bffd170f7c25a7373837040",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 6714,
          "name": "Jan Malkiewicz",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jan.malkiewicz@nokia.com",
          "username": "jmalkiewicz"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-12-01 14:13:11.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nSo let's merge it (and fix the problem) and than we can think it over where is the right place to put openssl. It we decide to move it will be do it separate commit, ok?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
